aVUsually, an activist hedge fund wants to oust the managers of a company it is battling to control -- not keep them. But William A. Ackman, founder of Pershing Square Capital Management, issued a statement last week lamenting the departure of Douglas M. Neve, chief financial officer of the Ceridian Corporation, the information services company. Calling Mr. Neve a ''first-class C.F.O.,'' Mr. Ackman said that his exit was ''a real disappointment,'' because he had overhauled the company's accounting and finances and improved margins at one of Ceridian's two key business units.
