aVThe White House said yesterday that it was reviewing a proposal by the Boeing Company and the General Electric Company to allow them to pursue a potential multimillion-dollar sale to Iran. The Washington Post reported yesterday that Iran had expressed interest in buying as many as 20 Boeing 737-400 passenger jets and their General Electric engines, which could be worth as much as $750 million. "We're reviewing it," said Dee Dee Myers, the White House press secretary.
