aVMOST CELEBRITIES hire themselves out as ''presenters'' in advertisments for the same reason most other people do. They get paid for it. Sometimes, though, there's more to it than that. Here is how a few celebrities view the work. CARY GRANT. Even though Mr. Grant has been a Faberge board member for 13 years, he has never done a commercial for the company, or for anyone else. ''Usually when I see a celebrity advertising a product I can't help thinking that he's endorsing his checks more than the product. If I did one it would be an institutional sort of campaign, for an entire company not just a certain product. I might say some nice things about General Electric, but I wouldn't stand and open the door of a refrigerator.''
