aVSCIENTISTS at the General Electric Company have found a way to generate more light by re-using some of the heat thrown off by a new type of light bulb. The new lamp, the company says, can reduce energy costs by up to 60 percent. A coating allows visible light to pass freely, but blocks the invisible radiation now emitted in the form of heat. With the heat retained inside, less electricity is needed to keep the filament glowing.
