aVBowater Inc. said yesterday that it would buy the Newsprint South Inc. paper mill in Grenada, Miss., from the General Electric Company's GE Capital Structured Finance Group for $370 million plus $8.9 million in debt. The mill, built in 1989, has an annual production capacity of about 250,000 metric tons of newsprint and has one of the lowest operating costs of a United States mill, the company said. Bowater, a paper manufacturer, said it expected the deal to close in the third quarter and that it would increase earnings and cash flow in the first year. With the Newsprint South acquisition, the company will have nine pulp and paper mills in the United States, Canada and South Korea.
