aVJohn F. Welch Jr., one of the most successful and highly compensated chief executives in corporate America, is about to be asked to defend how much he is paid to run the General Electric Company. A shareholder resolution seeking to eliminate a form of deferred compensation for Mr. Welch, G.E.'s chairman and chief executive, will be in the proxy statement that G.E. is expected to mail to shareholders in the next few days.
p1964
aVThe Federal Energy Regulatory Commission approved the Enron Corporation's $3.2 billion purchase of the Portland General Corporation yesterday, using for the first time a procedure intended to speed up the glacial pace of adjudicating utility mergers. It is also the first approval of a merger between a natural gas company and an electrical utility, a step that -- coupled with the new procedure -- could intensify an interest in such mergers that began last year.
