aVNew-media companies have had few friends lately. Much of the optimism of a year or so ago that information and entertainment sites on the World Wide Web could quickly lure big audiences and piles of money has evaporated. Particularly since October, when Wired Ventures Ltd., a champion of Internet culture in its magazine and on its on-line service, was forced to shelve its plans for an initial public offering, the business prospects for Internet companies have seemed bleak. This year, analysts predict, will bring a death knell for many Web sites.
