aVA late rebound gave Wall Street modest gains yesterday as two acquisitions and upbeat earnings from Hewlett-Packard helped lift some major market indexes to four-year highs. The indexes had their fourth consecutive winning week. Lower oil prices also helped stocks, easing worries about consumer spending ahead of the holiday shopping season. But many analysts remain split over whether the market will have its usual year-end rally, and trading has become erratic as mixed economic and earnings data leave investors wondering about the economy's health.
