aVFrench officials will go to Peking on Aug. 19 to bid for a stake in the construction of China's first nuclear power station, a Government spokesman said today. The French company Framatome would construct the nuclear part of the plant, while Alsthom-Atlantique would be responsible for other work on the Guangdong province station. Competing for the contract are Rheinisch-Westfalisches Elektrizitatswerk, the Westinghouse Electric Corporation and the General Electric Company of Britain, the spokesman said.
