VThe Ford Motor Company of Canada Ltd. said it had laid off 4,700 workers at two assembly plants here for one week, and that they would return to work Sept. 20. It said it had idled 3,000 car assembly workers because of a shortage of certain auto parts and 1,700 truck assembly workers to reduce high inventories. In other layoffs, the Manville Corporation's Johns-Manville of Canada unit said it had laid off 500 workers permanently at its mine in Asbestos, Quebec, and the General Electric Company announced the indefinite layoff of 733 workers at its Appliance Park facility in Louisville, Ky., reducing employment there to 10,200.
