VInterest rates declined modestly yesterday, but for most credit market participants the day's real excitement came about 3:30 P.M. when a power failure hit lower Manhattan. ''This market has been trading in the dark for a while, but this is ridiculous,'' one Government securities dealer said. After the lights and electronic display screens went blank, dealers said activity quickly came to a stop. ''We rely on the screens, and nobody trades or makes quotes without them,'' another securities dealer said.
