aVWHITE PLAINS, N.Y. JOHN SUSKO, as the photographs papering his office attest, has played on the Maxwell House football team. Also the softball team, the tennis team, the basketball team and the baseball team. At one time or another, he has captained them all. Off the field, Mr. Susko is being judged on both the qualities thus represented: leadership and teamwork. The sandy-haired, sunburned 30-year-old is a brand manager for Maxwell House instant, which is the best-selling instant coffee in the United States and part of the coffee division of General Foods, critically important to the company. As such, he must tread the line between pushing his own product and playing in the larger context of corporate wellbeing. ''We're fighting Maxwell House regular, Sanka, Brim,'' he said, citing some of the division's leading brands. But at the same time, he added, ''we look at ourselves as part of the Maxwell House Coffee Company.''
