aVThe General Electric Company announced a new system that can beam data from one building to another within a close range using highfrequency microwaves. G.E. said the typical uses for the system would include television conferences between exectives in two buildings within the same city, or a bank beaming a picture of a signature to a central office for verification. Transmission distance is limited to six-tenths of a mile for video transmission and two miles for data transmission, although G.E. said it expects to double that range by the end of the year. G.E. said it also expects eventually to give its system the ability to transmit sound, bringing it into more direct competition with telephone utilities for local calls.
