aVA shareholders group said it intends to ask the General Dynamics Corporation to disclose at its annual meeting on May 7 all chemicals in use at its Electric Boat division in Groton, Conn., and any employee health problems there. The group charged that employees at the giant submarine-building yard have been exposed to toxic substances such as beryllium and lead, and that millions of dollars of claims have been filed against the company in connection with asbestos-related diseases. Directors of the aerospace giant said they would recommend that shareholders reject the request as having ''no useful purpose.''
