aVTHE SCM Corporation, the typewriter company that over the years has added Proctor Silex appliances, Durkee foods, Allied paper and Glidden paints and chemicals, has dismayed some shareholders with this diversity. While a well-diversified company is recession-resistant, in times of prosperity the corporate convoy never travels with the speed of its fastest vessels. Besides, Wall Street likes simplicity - the pure play, if you will - and tends to shun complicated corporate setups. In short, Wall Street is not overly smitten with conglomerates.
