p2725
aVAfter working on robot technology for 22 years at the General Electric Company, Ralph Mosher left in 1971 to form Robotics Inc. and began producing heavy industrial robots. He sold about a dozen before running into financing problems and the 1974-75 recession. At that point, he switched to making a device to seal auto engine gaskets. Sales have been booming and now he plans to pump some of the profits back into robots and carve out his own special niche in the market. Specifically, he is developing a line of inexpensive, benchassembly robots that he hopes to introduce in 1982.
