aVThree executives were sentenced to prison terms today in a $1.25 million bribery scheme intended to enhance the General Electric Company's bid for a contract to build a Puerto Rican electric-generating plant. United States District Judge Anne Thompson fined G.E. $31,000. A G.E. subcontractor on the project, Schenectady Turbine Services Ltd. of Schenectady, and the executives also were fined $31,000 each. The judge refused to stay the fines pending an appeal.
