aVA tentative settlement has been reached in 16 lawsuits filed in Delaware by shareholders of the RCA Corporation regarding the proposed acquisition of RCA by the General Electric Company. The dispute involved RCA's agreement to give G.E. an option to buy 28.3 million shares at $53.125 a share if G.E.'s $66.50-a-share offer was topped by another bidder or in some way compromised by any major change in RCA's assets. The settlement, if approved by the Delaware court, would raise the price that G.E. would have to pay to $59.75 a share, the closing price of RCA's shares on the New York Stock Exchange on Dec. 11, the day the bid was announced.
