aVMismanagement in construction of the stalled Zimmer nuclear power plant is responsible for costs ranging from $1.3 billion to the full $1.72 billion spent on the project so far, according to a management audit ordered by the Public Utilities Commission of Ohio. The report is evidently the second attempt by state authorities to determine how much of the huge cost overruns at nuclear plants should be borne by electricity customers and how much should be borne by utility stockholders. Earlier this year the staff of the New York Public Utility Commission said that as much as $1.9 billion of the estimated $4.1 billion nuclear plant at Shoreham, L.I., had been ''imprudently'' spent and was not recoverable from rate payers. Lilco Issue Is Still Pending The Long Island Lighting Company, builder of the Shoreham plant, has denied any imprudence and has said the entire cost of the plant should be carried by utility customers. The issue is still before the commission.
