aVThe Burlington Northern Santa Fe Corporation agreed yesterday to buy the Washington Central Railroad Company, which operates two stretches of track in Washington state, for about $40 million in stock and cash. One of the lines connects the 234 miles of track between Kennewick and Cle Elum, and an 85-mile segment connects Connell to Moses Lake. In a second deal, Burlington Northern, which is based in Fort Worth, said it would buy 150 new locomotives from the General Electric Company for about $200 million. Burlington Northern will use the engines to replace less efficient ones. Burlington Northern stock rose $2, to $84.50, yesterday on the New York Stock Exchange.
