aVSecretary of the Navy John F. Lehman Jr. announced today that he was suspending the signing of all new contracts at two major divisions of the General Dynamics Corporation because of ''pervasive'' business misconduct. In addition, the Secretary said he was canceling two missile contracts worth $22.5 million and putting them up for competitive bidding. But he said he saw no reason why the Navy and General Dynamics could not reach an agreement that would restore normal business relations in a few weeks, assuming the company did not choose to be ''confrontational and litigious.'' Mr. Lehman also said he was fining the company, the nation's third-largest military contractor, $676,283 for giving gratuities to Adm. Hyman Rickover, who directed the Navy's nuclear submarine program until he retired in 1981.
